<sections title="EclipseLink 2.4.0  (Juno) Release">

	<section class="title">
		<description>
			<h1>EclipseLink 2.4.0 - Juno</h1>
			<p> The EclipseLink 2.4 release builds on the
				increased developer
				flexibility and multitenant features first
				introduced in 2.3.
				EclipseLink now offers support for NoSQL, REST, JSON as well as
				additional tenant isolation modes for PaaS and SaaS cloud enabled
				application development.
			</p>
		</description>
	</section>

	<section class="main" name=" New and Noteworthy" image="/sequoyah/images/CC_news.png">

		<description>

			<table>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>RESTFul Persistence with JPA-RS</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						Developers using EclipseLink in their applications
						can now simply add the JPA-RS web fragment library into their web
						applications and get the automated exposure of a REST access that
						exposes their persistence unit with entities being implicitly
						converted into JSON or XML within the REST operations.
					</td>
					<td width="150">
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Development/2.4.0/JPA-RS">JPA Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>Tenant Isolation by Table, Schema, or Data Source</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						Developers can design and deploy applications where
						their persistent entities
						manage entities for multiple tenants in
						the same application with
						storage in tables per tenant uniquely
						identified by name or
						schema. Developers can now alternatively have
						their applications customize the data source used for different
						tenant's application instances.
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a
								href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/DesignDocs/Multi-Tenancy/TablePerTenant">JPA Documentation</a>
						</div>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/wiki_small.png" />
							<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Examples/JPA/Multitenant">JPA Example</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>

				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>Database Change Event Cache Invalidation</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						In Oracle Databases, caches will get automatically
						updated when the table changes.
					</td>
					<td>
						<!--<div> <img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" /> <a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/DesignDocs/356812">JPA 
							Documentation</a> </div> -->
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/wiki_small.png" />
							<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Examples/JPA/DCN">JPA Example</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>

				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>No SQL support</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						Support for using EclipseLink with NoSQL Databases.
						EclipseLink 2.4.0 provides initial support for Mongo and Oracle
						NoSQL.
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a
								href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/UserGuide/JPA/Advanced_JPA_Development/NoSQL/Persistence_Units">JPA Documentation</a>
						</div>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/wiki_small.png" />
							<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Examples/JPA/NoSQL">JPA Example</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>

		</description>

